author: Sean Shapiro
title: Bowie runners benefit from a pack mentality
text:
Last fall, Marissa Flournoy missed qualifying for the UIL cross-country championships by one spot when she finished 23rd at the Class 6A, Region II meet.
“That was tough,” Flournoy said recently. “I’m going to do everything I can to make it this year. Even if it kills me.”
